## 1. Duplicate `ColorValues` Extension

> [!CAUTION]
> The same `extension ColorValues on Color` is copy-pasted into **3 separate files**. This will cause **compile-time conflicts** if any file imports two of them.

| File | Lines |
|---|---|
| [doctors_list_screen.dart](file:///home/himanshu/Documents/Repositories/LabLedger/lib/screens/doctors/doctors_list_screen.dart#L18-L35) | 18–35 |
| [franchise_labs_list_screen.dart](file:///home/himanshu/Documents/Repositories/LabLedger/lib/screens/franchise_labs/franchise_labs_list_screen.dart#L17-L34) | 17–34 |
| [user_list_screen.dart](file:///home/himanshu/Documents/Repositories/LabLedger/lib/screens/profile/user_list_screen.dart#L17-L34) | 17–34 |

**What's wrong:** Dart's `Color` class already has `withValues()` in Flutter 3.x. This extension shadows the SDK method and will break when you upgrade Flutter.

**Recommendation:** Delete all three copies. Use the SDK-provided `Color.withValues()` or `Color.withAlpha()` directly.

