## 7. Duplicate Edit-Screen Header Card Pattern

> [!IMPORTANT]
> This is the **highest-impact** reusability opportunity. The exact same header card structure (avatar circle → title/subtitle/badges → save/delete buttons) is copy-pasted across **4 edit screens** (~80–100 lines each).

| File | Method | ~Lines |
|---|---|---|
| [category_edit_screen.dart](file:///home/himanshu/Documents/Repositories/LabLedger/lib/screens/categories/category_edit_screen.dart#L70-L211) | `_buildHeaderCard` | 140 |
| [doctor_edit_screen.dart](file:///home/himanshu/Documents/Repositories/LabLedger/lib/screens/doctors/doctor_edit_screen.dart#L181-L343) | `_buildDoctorHeaderCard` | 160 |
| [diagnosis_type_edit_screen.dart](file:///home/himanshu/Documents/Repositories/LabLedger/lib/screens/diagnosis_types/diagnosis_type_edit_screen.dart#L129-L255) | `_buildHeaderCard` | 125 |
| [franchise_edit_screen.dart](file:///home/himanshu/Documents/Repositories/LabLedger/lib/screens/franchise_labs/franchise_edit_screen.dart#L94-L252) | `_buildFranchiseHeaderCard` | 158 |

**What's wrong:** ~580 lines of nearly identical layout code. The only differences are: title, subtitle, initials, save/delete callbacks, and button labels.

**Recommendation:** Create a generic `EditScreenHeaderCard` widget:
```dart
class EditScreenHeaderCard extends StatelessWidget {
  final String title, subtitle, initials;
  final Color color;
  final bool isEditMode, isAdmin, isSaving, isDeleting;
  final VoidCallback? onSave, onDelete;
  final String saveLabel, deleteLabel;
  // ...
}
```
**Estimated savings:** ~450 lines.

