## 14. Three Competing Button Widgets

| Widget | File | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `CustomElevatedButton` | [custom_elevated_button.dart](file:///home/himanshu/Documents/Repositories/LabLedger/lib/screens/ui_components/custom_elevated_button.dart) | Simple elevated button with icon |
| `CustomOutlinedButton` | [custom_outlined_button.dart](file:///home/himanshu/Documents/Repositories/LabLedger/lib/screens/ui_components/custom_outlined_button.dart) | Hardcoded `error` color, fixed size |
| `CustomActionButton` | [custom_action_button.dart](file:///home/himanshu/Documents/Repositories/LabLedger/lib/screens/ui_components/custom_action_button.dart) | Uses `AppInkWell` + custom container |
| `ReusableButton` | [reusable_ui_components.dart](file:///home/himanshu/Documents/Repositories/LabLedger/lib/screens/ui_components/reusable_ui_components.dart#L148-L345) | Full variant system (6 variants) — **appears unused** |

**What's wrong:**
- `CustomOutlinedButton` hardcodes `error` color — not customizable.
- `ReusableButton` supports 6 variants but appears to be unused.
- `CustomActionButton` bypasses Flutter's button system entirely (no semantics, no disabled state).
- Edit screens sometimes use `CustomElevatedButton`, sometimes inline `ElevatedButton.icon` (inconsistent).

**Recommendation:** Either adopt `ReusableButton` as the single source of truth (it already supports all variants), or delete it and standardize the existing three buttons. Do not keep 4 competing button APIs.

